piskorski.util.set

Class SimpleIntSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • piskorski.util.set.SimpleIntSet

  • public final class SimpleIntSet
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    Jakub Piskorski This class is an efficient implementation of sorted integer sets. The functionality of this class is reduced to minimum. Further, the methods hashCode and equals have been overdriven.

    • Constructor Summary

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Overwrites the standard native hashCode() method from java.lang.Object, since it (usually) returns the internal memory address for this object (which does not suffice in our case, viz., using the data vectors as keys in a hash table and checking for structural equality); The code is borrowed from java.lang.String; the hash code for a data vector is computed as code[0]*31^(n-1) + code[1]*31^(n-2) + ... + code[n-1] using int arithmetic, where n is the length of code's int[]; note that the computation of the above polynom only works, because the int type does not signal an overflow (+, *, and ^ are "ring" operations)
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        the hash code value for this object
        See Also:
        String
